<div style="border-bottom: 2px solid #808080;     color: #000000;     float: left;     font-family: 'Sentinel A','Sentinel B';     font-size: 20px;     line-height: 25px;     margin: 0 0 20px;     padding: 0 0 15px;     width: 95%;" >
<span style="font-weight:bold;">#FreeExpressionIs </span>a right every writer should enjoy.
 But many, like Chinese Uyghur writer Ilham Tohti, 
 can't. That is why PEN American Center is challenging
 our supporters to use Twitter to define, describe,
 visualize, or imagine the value of Freedom of Expression.
</div>

<div style="float: left;width: 95%;">
            <div id="win_tix_hdr" style="color: #B83101;     float: left;     font-family: 'Verlag A','Verlag B';     font-size: 30px;     line-height: 35px;     text-align: right;     text-transform: uppercase;     width: 223px; margin-right:35px">
			win tickets
                        to&nbsp;pen's
			literary gala
			</div>

			<div style="display:inline;">
						 <p style="font-family: 'Sentinel A','Sentinel B';font-size: 15px;">
The user who best captures the spirit of free expression in a tweet with the hashtag #FreeExpressionIs by <span style="color: #B83101;">Saturday, May 3 at 11:59pmEDT</span> will receive tickets to PEN's Literary Gala on May 5*, where PEN will honor Twitter CEO Dick Costolo, as well as Ilham Tohti and acclaimed novelist Salman Rushdie.
							 
						 </br>
						 <p style="font-style: italic;">*Tickets to the 2015 Literary Gala may be substituted upon request.</p>
